content.description: A few mixed routes in the 5.10 range were established here by Danny Meyers and Jenni Stone in the late 80s after the first Keyhole Classic. This is the last  and tallest wall on the south end of the west facing trachyandesite dyke just before it disappears into the hillside.  A tower of volcanic breccia rests against the middle of the cliff and the routes are on either side of it.
